# Combining Parent & Child

Sometimes, you don't want to *erase* the parent's logic. You want to run the parent's logic, and THEN add your own stuff on top!

To literally trigger the Parent's version of the code, you use `super.methodName()`.

```swift
override func attack() {
    // Run the parent's normal 10 damage first
    super.attack()

    // Then add the new Boss logic
    print("And a Boss Stomp for 50 more damage!")
}
```
